        "score": 0.6687057,
        "text": "The document outlines procedures related to the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT) regarding user fees and transmission billing determinants.\n\n1. **User Fees:**\n   - ERCOT is required to post user fees approved by the ERCOT Board on its website within two business days of any changes.\n   - Market Participants or other entities must pay these approved user fees.\n\n2. **Transmission Billing Determinant Calculation:**\n   - ERCOT provides Market Participants with necessary parameters and formulas to calculate billing charges for using Transmission or Distribution Facilities.\n   - ERCOT is not responsible for billing, collection, or disbursal of payments for transmission access service.\n\n3. **Billing Determinant Data Elements:**\n   - ERCOT calculates and provides data elements annually for Transmission Service Providers (TSPs) and Distribution Service Providers (DSPs) to use as billing determinants.\n   - Data must be provided by December 1 each year and comply with specific regulatory requirements.\n   - Key data elements include:\n     - The 4-Coincident Peak (4-CP) for each DSP and External Load Serving Entity (ELSE).\n     - The ERCOT average 4-CP.\n     - The average 4-CP for each DSP and ELSE coincident to the ERCOT average 4-CP.\n   - The ERCOT average 4-CP is the average of the coincidental MW peaks during June, July, August, and September.\n   - Coincidental MW peak is defined as the highest monthly Settlement Interval 15-minute MW peak for the entire ERCOT Transmission Grid, calculated using a specific formula involving net energy production and transfers.\n\nThe document also references updates to be made in accordance with NPRR995 and NPRR1188.",
        "metadata": {
