klist ... • Part 3: Request to Commission a Resource • Resources requesting commercial operation outside of the Summer and Winter seasons do not need to submit a declaration of weather preparedness for Part 3 Approval. • Those new resources can be declared together with other existing resources during the May 1 – Jun 1 and Nov 1 – Dec 1 semi-annual declaration of weather preparedness submittal windows. Generator has now completed the interconnection process.\nPUBLIC\nSmall Generation Process\n14 The Small Generation process is governed by Planning Guide Section 5.4. RIOO-IS Small Generation Initial Application Checks: ... • Signed Declaration of Department of Defense (DOD) Notification \n• Payment for Small Gen application ... [FRT and VRT] and Planning Guide Section 5.4.2)\n• Resource Data Submission – Entered into RIOO by IE/RE • Include the TDSP Station Name and Code for the Resource Site Name/Code • All Operation Limitations should be reflected \n• Include Load Resource INR if BESS (Until ESR data entry is created) PUBLIC\nResource Integration page\n15\nPUBLIC\nResource Interconnection Handbook\n16\nGeneration Interconnection Requests\n17 1,881 active generation interconnection requests totaling 372 GW as of September 30th, 2024 (Solar 154 GW, Wind 35 GW, Gas 26 GW, and Battery 154 GW) (Excludes capacity associated with projects designated as Inactive per Planning Guide Section 5.7.6) Generation Interconnection Request"
